The paper discusses a new approach to reinforcement learning that combines model-based and model-free paradigms. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on robotics and control, which fall under the cs.RO and cs.SY sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses neural networks, which are a common tool in reinforcement learning, and thus the cs.NE sub-category is also a likely fit.
